  <brief_title>Effect of Chronic Oral Hydration in Patients With Recurrent Unexplained Syncope</brief_title>
  <official_title>Benefit of Controlled Rehydration in Unexplained Syncope</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>University Hospital, Angers</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University Hospital, Angers</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Beneficial effect of chronic hydration with salt supplementation in patients with recurrent
      unexplained syncope is not established. We sought to determine if chronic oral rehydration
      with salt supplementation improved the tolerance and hemodynamic responses of patients with
      unexplained recurrent syncope.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
